// Livepeer Payments v1 — PayerDaemon service.
//
// The PayerDaemon runs next to a payer application — a Livepeer gateway
// or any consumer app paying an orchestrator. It creates and signs
// tickets, manages per-session sender nonces, and watches the payer's
// on-chain escrow.
//
// Mounted only when the daemon is started with `--mode=sender`. Calls
// to it in receiver mode return UNIMPLEMENTED.
